cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval, which involves multiple modalities such as text and images. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.IR is the most likely category as the paper focuses on retrieval tasks and similarity measures. cs.CV and cs.CL are also likely categories as they deal with image and text processing, respectively. cs.LG and cs.MM are less likely but still possible categories as they also deal with machine learning and multimedia, respectively.
